## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

---

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 1 (systemic — affects 7 of 10 tests) |
| **Medium** | 1 |
| **Low** | 1 |

This test class is a textbook example of **coverage touching** — every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called, but almost nothing is actually verified. This explains your 95% coverage + production bugs perfectly.

---

### 🔴 CRITICAL: Coverage Touching / Missing Assertions

**7 of 10 tests** either have **no assertion at all** or only assert `IsNotNull` (which for value types / non-nullable returns can never fail).

| Test Method | Problem |
|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | Zero assertions. Only proves no exception was thrown. |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33-36) | Zero assertions. Never checks the price actually changed. |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39-43) | Zero assertions. Never checks the product is gone. |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L64-66) | Zero assertions. Doesn't even capture the count. |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L69-74) | Zero assertions. Never verifies prices were reduced. |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L85-88) | Zero assertions. Never checks the product was imported. |
| `GetProduct_Works` (L24-29) | Only `Assert.IsNotNull`. Never checks SKU, Name, or Price match. |
| `SearchProducts_Works` (L47-52) | Only `Assert.IsNotNull`. Never checks the list contains "Widget" or its count. |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55-60) | Only `Assert.IsNotNull`. Never checks the count is 1. |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` (L77-82) | Only `Assert.IsNotNull`. Never checks CSV content. |

**Why this is Critical:** These tests will pass even if `UpdatePrice` is a no-op, `RemoveProduct` doesn't delete, `ApplyBulkDiscount` multiplies instead of discounting, or `ImportFromCsv` silently drops data. You have **code coverage without behavioral coverage**.

**Concrete fixes:**

```csharp
// BEFORE — AddProduct_Works
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// AFTER — verifies the product is retrievable with correct data
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_ProductIsRetrievable()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", retrieved?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, retrieved?.Price);
}
```

```csharp
// BEFORE — UpdatePrice_Works
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

// AFTER — verifies the mutation persisted
